This paper involves natural language processing (NLP) and computer vision (CV) techniques to enable robots to navigate in human environments. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the sub-categories of cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). Additionally, the paper involves the use of machine learning algorithms to train agents to navigate in these environments, which falls under the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, since the paper deals with the navigation of robots, it is also likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.RO (Robotics).
